## Workflow Diagram Maintenance

### When to Update Workflow Diagrams

**REQUIRED**: Update the relevant workflow diagram when:

1. **Status Changes**: When a planned page becomes implemented, change status from 🚧 to ✅
2. **Implementation Deviates**: If actual implementation differs from planned workflow, update the diagram
3. **New Collections**: If new Firestore collections are added, document them in integration points
4. **New Storage Paths**: If new Storage paths are used, document them
5. **New Integrations**: If new cross-module relationships are created, document them
6. **Feature Changes**: If features are added/removed/modified, update the diagram

### How to Update Workflow Diagrams

1. Open the relevant `workflows/workflow-admin-*.md` file
2. Update the Mermaid flowchart if workflow changed
3. Update the "Planned Features" section (if planned) or add "Implemented Features" (if implemented)
4. Update "Integration Points" with actual collections/paths used
5. Update "Related Pages" if new relationships created
6. Update "Implementation Notes" with actual technical decisions
7. Update `workflows/README.md` if status changed (✅ vs 🚧)

